            <translation>Christian Ratz knows where those books of Paracelsus are. As Georgius Marquarolus told me, 20 February 1567. Paracelsus's 'Archidoxa' and 'Liber de renovatione et restauratione', the 'Morborum commentarii',
                the first book of 'Von naturlichen dingen', the 'Book on the virtues of minerals' in medicine, the 'Liber de nascentibus ex terra', 'Elf trakat von Ursprung', 'On divine provindence in the consideration of the 
                structure of the world and all its creatures', 'Of the fourteen gradations of Paracelsus', 'Book on Mucilage', and other fragments of Paracelsus. 'De transmutatione metallorum', has also arrived at another place, yet at a more fitting time.
            John has: 1) 'De creatione hominis' 2) 'Paragranum'.</translation>
